{"article_id":"j1ThWumdXqYxGG4R","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"President Donald Trump came to the conclusion","depth":4},{"id":1,"text":"that Supreme Court nominee Brett Kavanuagh needed to be confirmed","depth":5},{"id":2,"text":"to avoid depressing GOP turnout in November .","depth":5},{"id":3,"text":"|","depth":4},{"id":4,"text":"AP Photo/Alex Brandon White House","depth":4},{"id":5,"text":"How Trump saved Kavanaugh","depth":3},{"id":6,"text":"The president was convinced","depth":9},{"id":7,"text":"that the cost to his administration and the GOP would be too great","depth":10},{"id":8,"text":"if he abandoned the judge ,","depth":10},{"id":9,"text":"aides said .","depth":8},{"id":10,"text":"Fox News anchors said","depth":9},{"id":11,"text":"Christine Blasey Ford ' s testimony was compelling .","depth":9},{"id":12,"text":"Republican strategists sent panicked text messages","depth":10},{"id":13,"text":"anticipating an electoral disaster .","depth":10},{"id":14,"text":"And even some Brett Kavanaugh supporters questioned","depth":10},{"id":15,"text":"whether he could rescue his nomination .","depth":10},{"id":16,"text":"But","depth":8},{"id":17,"text":"as Kavanaugh ' s nomination to the Supreme Court appeared to be crumbling under the weight of sexual assault accusations ,","depth":9},{"id":18,"text":"President Donald Trump had already become convinced","depth":10},{"id":19,"text":"that abandoning the judge would come at too great a cost to his administration and his party ' s chances in the midterm elections .","depth":10},{"id":20,"text":"The president ,","depth":11},{"id":21,"text":"according to half a dozen officials and people","depth":12},{"id":22,"text":"working on the confirmation ,","depth":12},{"id":23,"text":"came to the determination","depth":10},{"id":24,"text":"that","depth":10},{"id":25,"text":"with the midterms rapidly approaching ,","depth":11},{"id":26,"text":"he needed the Senate to confirm the conservative justice","depth":11},{"id":27,"text":"to avoid depressing GOP turnout come November .","depth":8},{"id":28,"text":"White House aides and allies conceded","depth":8},{"id":29,"text":"that throughout the touch-and-go confirmation battle , they weren ' t sure","depth":9},{"id":30,"text":"whether Kavanaugh would hold on in the face of the sexual assault allegations and the prevailing # MeToo movement","depth":10},{"id":31,"text":"that has swept the country for more than a year .","depth":10},{"id":32,"text":"But","depth":8},{"id":33,"text":"with Sen. Susan Collins","depth":13},{"id":34,"text":"( R-Maine )","depth":13},{"id":35,"text":"coming out in support of Kavanaugh Friday afternoon","depth":12},{"id":36,"text":"- giving the judge enough votes","depth":12},{"id":37,"text":"to get through -","depth":12},{"id":38,"text":"Trump ' s gamble","depth":11},{"id":39,"text":"to stand with him","depth":11},{"id":40,"text":"has conservatives feeling","depth":10},{"id":41,"text":"like they narrowly escaped catastrophe .","depth":10},{"id":42,"text":"\" Abandoning Kavanaugh under the existing circumstances would have demoralized the base , \"","depth":8},{"id":43,"text":"said Saul Anuzis , a former chairman of the Michigan Republican Party .","depth":8},{"id":44,"text":"\" One can second-guess individual tactics ,","depth":8},{"id":45,"text":"but the Kavanaugh confirmation process ,","depth":11},{"id":46,"text":"win or lose ,","depth":11},{"id":47,"text":"has been helpful","depth":10},{"id":48,"text":"in waking up a lethargic Republican Party . \"","depth":9},{"id":49,"text":"Republican strategists said","depth":7},{"id":50,"text":"the bruising fight is resonating with their voters","depth":7},{"id":51,"text":"- a far cry from the feeling early on ,","depth":7},{"id":52,"text":"when some worried","depth":8},{"id":53,"text":"the judge ' s confirmation would slide through so seamlessly","depth":9},{"id":54,"text":"that few on the right would even remember .","depth":9},{"id":55,"text":"Now ,","depth":7},{"id":56,"text":"they say ,","depth":7},{"id":57,"text":"even some voters less favorable to the president are being jolted .","depth":6},{"id":58,"text":"Playbook newsletter","depth":3},{"id":59,"text":"Sign up today","depth":5},{"id":60,"text":"to receive the # 1-rated newsletter in politics","depth":5},{"id":61,"text":"Email Sign Up","depth":5},{"id":62,"text":"By signing up","depth":8},{"id":63,"text":"you agree to receive email newsletters or alerts from .","depth":8},{"id":64,"text":"You can unsubscribe at any time .","depth":7},{"id":65,"text":"This site is protected by reCAPTCHA","depth":7},{"id":66,"text":"and the Google Privacy Policy and Terms of Service apply .","depth":7},{"id":67,"text":"White House officials have been reviewing polling on the narrowing so-called enthusiasm gap between Republicans and already motivated Democrats in key states .","depth":7},{"id":68,"text":"A person familiar with the numbers contended","depth":11},{"id":69,"text":"that GOP fervor is peaking at the right moment :","depth":11},{"id":70,"text":"Early and absentee voting is underway ,","depth":11},{"id":71,"text":"or starting up , in Arizona , Ohio , Iowa , Montana and Indiana .","depth":11},{"id":72,"text":"House Republican operatives pointed to a surge in fundraising over the final week of September ,","depth":10},{"id":73,"text":"including a text message","depth":11},{"id":74,"text":"that raised seven times what such solicitations typically average .","depth":11},{"id":75,"text":"Chris Wilson , the Republican pollster , said","depth":9},{"id":76,"text":"GOP enthusiasm is up 100,000 voters in Texas ,","depth":10},{"id":77,"text":"and he ' s also seen positive growth in North Dakota , Montana , Nevada and Arizona .","depth":10},{"id":78,"text":"In Georgia ,","depth":10},{"id":79,"text":"where a new statewide poll found","depth":11},{"id":80,"text":"49 percent say","depth":12},{"id":81,"text":"they support confirming the judge ,","depth":12},{"id":82,"text":"political warfare over Kavanaugh 's fate is having a \" boomerang effect \" on Democrats ,","depth":9},{"id":83,"text":"said Mark Rountree , a GOP strategist .","depth":8},{"id":84,"text":"The state is in the middle of a tense governor ' s race ,","depth":8},{"id":85,"text":"where Republican Brian Kemp is running neck-and-neck with Democrat Stacey Abrams .","depth":8},{"id":86,"text":"Had Kavanaugh ' s nomination been withdrawn ,","depth":7},{"id":87,"text":"Rountree said","depth":8},{"id":88,"text":"the fallout may have been similar to the moment last year","depth":9},{"id":89,"text":"when Republicans were \" deflated","depth":10},{"id":90,"text":"after [ the late Sen. John ] McCain gave the thumbs down to repealing Obamacare . \"","depth":10},{"id":91,"text":"Whether it ' s enough","depth":8},{"id":92,"text":"to counterbalance a gathering blue wave","depth":8},{"id":93,"text":"is unknown .","depth":7},{"id":94,"text":"Democrats during the confirmation process pointed to massive fundraising hauls and polling","depth":9},{"id":95,"text":"they believe","depth":10},{"id":96,"text":"positions them well for November .","depth":10},{"id":97,"text":"But buttressing the GOP strategists ' confidence is their view","depth":12},{"id":98,"text":"that Senate Democrats took a powerful issue","depth":13},{"id":99,"text":"and overplayed their hand -","depth":13},{"id":100,"text":"\" the demonstrators and protesters were too radical , \"","depth":12},{"id":101,"text":"Anuzis said .","depth":12},{"id":102,"text":"\" It was too obvious , too calculating and too much according to articulated political plans , \"","depth":11},{"id":103,"text":"he said .","depth":11},{"id":104,"text":"\" Trying to demonize a federal judge , with a distinguished career , for what he may or may not have done in high school didn ' t seem credible .","depth":10},{"id":105,"text":"Everybody has memories of their high school and college days","depth":11},{"id":106,"text":"that they would love to do over . \"","depth":11},{"id":107,"text":"Getting Trump supporters to that viewpoint took patience , though ,","depth":9},{"id":108,"text":"which hasn ' t always been a virtue for the White House .","depth":9},{"id":109,"text":"Publicly , Trump and others from the administration made clear","depth":10},{"id":110,"text":"that it ultimately fell to Kavanaugh to personally explain himself .","depth":10},{"id":111,"text":"And some of his attempts flopped .","depth":10},{"id":112,"text":"A Fox News interview , for instance , was considered a mistake inside and outside the White House in terms of his tone , delivery and content .","depth":12},{"id":113,"text":"A person","depth":15},{"id":114,"text":"involved in the confirmation","depth":15},{"id":115,"text":"recalled worrying","depth":14},{"id":116,"text":"that it made Kavanaugh appear shifty ,","depth":14},{"id":117,"text":"while exposing him to new lines of questioning from critics and the Senate Judiciary Committee .","depth":14},{"id":118,"text":"Some of the judge ' s classmates told reporters","depth":13},{"id":119,"text":"it helped draw them out of the woodwork","depth":14},{"id":120,"text":"to offer unflattering character assessments","depth":14},{"id":121,"text":"because they disliked the phony choir-boy image","depth":13},{"id":122,"text":"he projected .","depth":13},{"id":123,"text":"Kavanaugh backed away from the wholesome persona in what the White House considered his \" make or break \" moment before the Senate committee last week ,","depth":9},{"id":124,"text":"when he countered Ford ' s account of sexual assault .","depth":9},{"id":125,"text":"The judge ' s remarks delighted the president","depth":10},{"id":126,"text":"and helped buoy people inside the White House","depth":11},{"id":127,"text":"who believed him all along","depth":12},{"id":128,"text":"but felt","depth":13},{"id":129,"text":"he needed to make clear the stakes of the battle ,","depth":13},{"id":130,"text":"aides said .","depth":9},{"id":131,"text":"After that , Trump went into a string of rallies","depth":9},{"id":132,"text":"feeling better about his chances","depth":10},{"id":133,"text":"of reshaping the court ,","depth":10},{"id":134,"text":"telling close associates","depth":11},{"id":135,"text":"he believed","depth":11},{"id":136,"text":"West Virginia Sen. Joe Manchin , a Democrat","depth":13},{"id":137,"text":"facing a difficult reelection in a state","depth":14},{"id":138,"text":"that heavily favors Trump ,","depth":14},{"id":139,"text":"was running a tough campaign","depth":12},{"id":140,"text":"and would vote with Republicans .","depth":11},{"id":141,"text":"Manchin indicated his support Friday .","depth":9},{"id":142,"text":"The White House and outside allies came to see Senate Democrats ' shifting demands","depth":9},{"id":143,"text":"- from initially advocating for an FBI investigation into the charges ,","depth":10},{"id":144,"text":"to criticizing the tight timeline","depth":12},{"id":145,"text":"once Republicans acquiesced to a probe ,","depth":12},{"id":146,"text":"to finally dismissing it as a sham -","depth":11},{"id":147,"text":"as helping convince equivocal senators","depth":9},{"id":148,"text":"that no amount of due diligence was going to satisfy the judge ' s critics .","depth":9},{"id":149,"text":"Democrats dispute these characterizations ,","depth":9},{"id":150,"text":"arguing","depth":10},{"id":151,"text":"the deck was stacked against conducting a thorough investigation .","depth":10},{"id":152,"text":"But Trump ' s allies said","depth":9},{"id":153,"text":"the wall-to-wall media coverage of the original allegations and Democrats ' changing strategies ,","depth":11},{"id":154,"text":"followed by the flood of articles","depth":12},{"id":155,"text":"concentrating on other uncorroborated charges","depth":13},{"id":156,"text":"and incorporating the judge ' s alcohol drinking habits as a youth ,","depth":13},{"id":157,"text":"helped delegitimize the more serious accusations .","depth":10},{"id":158,"text":"\" I know","depth":10},{"id":159,"text":"Trump likes to take on the press for both political and practical reasons ,","depth":11},{"id":160,"text":"but not everybody in the White House does , \"","depth":11},{"id":161,"text":"said David Bozell , president of the conservative group ForAmerica .","depth":9},{"id":162,"text":"The strategy focused on using Trump","depth":12},{"id":163,"text":"to stand behind Kavanaugh","depth":12},{"id":164,"text":"as momentum turned against the judge ,","depth":11},{"id":165,"text":"while torquing the overall message toward the on-the-fence senators .","depth":10},{"id":166,"text":"\" Remember the audience , \"","depth":11},{"id":167,"text":"one ally said earlier this week","depth":11},{"id":168,"text":"when focus returned to the president .","depth":10},{"id":169,"text":"Another Republican close to the process said","depth":10},{"id":170,"text":"the White House knew","depth":11},{"id":171,"text":"it needed Trump ' s bullhorn","depth":12},{"id":172,"text":"to magnify the message in an intense and diffuse media environment .","depth":12},{"id":173,"text":"Although they admitted","depth":11},{"id":174,"text":"that nearly every time","depth":13},{"id":175,"text":"Trump engaged","depth":13},{"id":176,"text":"was a gamble","depth":12},{"id":177,"text":"- fanning fears","depth":11},{"id":178,"text":"that he might irrevocably offend Republicans","depth":12},{"id":179,"text":"whose votes were crucial for the judge ' s confirmation .","depth":12},{"id":180,"text":"After Trump sent a Sept. 21 tweet","depth":13},{"id":181,"text":"challenging the credibility of Kavanaugh ' s first accuser ,","depth":13},{"id":182,"text":"Collins","depth":15},{"id":183,"text":"- one of the few undecided GOP senators at the time -","depth":15},{"id":184,"text":"said","depth":14},{"id":185,"text":"she was \" appalled. \"","depth":13},{"id":186,"text":"Later , Collins called it \" just plain wrong \"","depth":13},{"id":187,"text":"when Trump ' s mocked Ford at a rally in Mississippi ,","depth":13},{"id":188,"text":"repeating the phrase","depth":13},{"id":189,"text":"\" I don ' t remember . \"","depth":13},{"id":190,"text":"The Mississippi rally also miffed other undecided Republicans","depth":11},{"id":191,"text":"- Sen. Jeff Flake called it \" appalling , \"","depth":13},{"id":192,"text":"though he ultimately supported the judge ,","depth":13},{"id":193,"text":"while Alaska Sen. Lisa Murkowski said","depth":13},{"id":194,"text":"she would oppose Kavanaugh ' s confirmation ,","depth":14},{"id":195,"text":"deeming it \" wholly inappropriate . \"","depth":14},{"id":196,"text":"Trump ' s rally antics came","depth":11},{"id":197,"text":"only a few days after he called Ford \" very credible. \"","depth":11},{"id":198,"text":"Yet aides said","depth":11},{"id":199,"text":"Trump 's lines","depth":13},{"id":200,"text":"denouncing Ford ,","depth":14},{"id":201,"text":"and supporting Kavanaugh ,","depth":14},{"id":202,"text":"generated some of the night 's largest applause breaks .","depth":12},{"id":203,"text":"As the process drew out ,","depth":6},{"id":204,"text":"those involved in the confirmation also indicated","depth":7},{"id":205,"text":"they were less concerned about turning off female voters ,","depth":8},{"id":206,"text":"and instead tried to reframe the debate around wrongly accused men .","depth":8},{"id":207,"text":"Trump and his allies asked Americans to consider how they would feel","depth":7},{"id":208,"text":"if their family members were falsely accused of sexual assault .","depth":7},{"id":209,"text":"\" It is a very scary time for young men in America ,","depth":9},{"id":210,"text":"where you can be guilty of something","depth":10},{"id":211,"text":"you may not be guilty of , \"","depth":10},{"id":212,"text":"Trump told reporters Tuesday .","depth":8},{"id":213,"text":"\" What ' s happening here has much more to do than even the appointment of a Supreme Court justice . \"","depth":7},{"id":214,"text":"Kavanaugh also maintained strong support from White House counsel Don McGahn and Federalist Society Executive Director Leonard Leo , two powerful individuals","depth":6},{"id":215,"text":"who recommended the judge for the high court .","depth":6},{"id":216,"text":"In the end , the confirmation gives Trump another bullet point a month before the midterms , something","depth":7},{"id":217,"text":"the president can take to the rallies","depth":8},{"id":218,"text":"he ' s lining up across the country .","depth":8},{"id":219,"text":"It also gives down-ballot candidates a talking point ,","depth":8},{"id":220,"text":"if they chose to deploy it .","depth":8},{"id":221,"text":"\" They are going to be talking about the Supreme Court -","depth":10},{"id":222,"text":"if Republicans sell this success , \"","depth":10},{"id":223,"text":"Bozell said .","depth":9},{"id":224,"text":"\" It ' s going to be up to them to sell the passage of this . \"","depth":8}],"relations":[{"parent":449,"left":282,"right":448,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":282,"left":229,"right":281,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":229,"left":227,"right":228,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":227,"left":0,"right":226,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":226,"left":1,"right":2,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":228,"left":3,"right":4,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":281,"left":5,"right":280,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":280,"left":271,"right":279,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":271,"left":250,"right":270,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":250,"left":238,"right":249,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":238,"left":232,"right":237,"relation":"explanation","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":232,"left":231,"right":9,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":231,"left":6,"right":230,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":230,"left":7,"right":8,"relation